message: Moonballs - the No 1 and 2 rankings on this page are based on the rankings of the major, recognized ranking authorities AT THE TIME; Your continual changes do not accurately reflect those.  In 1990, Edberg was clearly superior to Lendl in the ATP points (Lendl was third) and was ranked by the the highly regarded Tennis Mag as No. 1 with Lendl only No. 3 behind Agassi.  At the time everyone agreed the ITF ranking was incorrect and politically based.  Please stop making these changes.
